    "updated_at": "2024-07-22T08:21:30Z",
    "body": "Same problem. This only happens when `ssh` into a terminal with starship. Other thing I found it necessary for reproducing the problem:\r\n\r\n- zsh 5.9\r\n- ssh, and the first shell (the nested shell works fine)\r\n- starship\r\n\r\nIn my case, I can reproduce the problem when sshing into Ubuntu. So I think OS X is not the main reason.\r\n\r\nHow to fix this issue, temporarily:\r\n\r\nAdd these to `starship.toml`:\r\n\r\n```toml\r\n[character]\r\n# Use any ASCII characters.\r\nsuccess_symbol = '[->](bold green)'\r\nerror_symbol = '[->](bold red)'\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt seems that zsh 5.9 somehow does not recognize the true width of some Unicode characters like \"❯\", which is the default leading character in starship.\r\n\r\nYou can try to paste the symbol \"❯\" to your remote shell and get:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"332\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2c8edcdc-9faf-49f3-bd06-381356fcb814\">\r\n\r\nBut if you invoke a subshell with `zsh`, then it can be correctly displayed:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"338\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c56b4e12-ac66-4621-bcc8-b9acf5f9b4df\">\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nEdit: related issue https://github.com/starship/starship/issues/5963. So the bug is caused by the locale setup.\r\n",
