    "updated_at": "2024-07-22T10:27:47Z",
    "body": "Sshing into nixos system works fine. So might be just non-nixos systems.\r\n\r\nAlso see https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/issues/19785 - wondering if this might be connected.\r\n\r\nIn particular, I encountered that bug because when logging, zsh initializes its terminfo settings. But initially - at least for alacritty -  TERM points to an invalid entry, because `$TERMINFO_DIRS` hasn't been initialized yet.\r\n\r\nThen as part of loading the shell we set `$TERMINFO_DIRS`, but it is too late now, we already tried to load the terminfo settings, we are not doing to try again.\r\n\r\nAccording to the bug report calling `TERM=$TERM` should fix this. At one stage I had to put a `sleep 1` in the `.zshenv` first. No idea why. But seems that just `TERM=$TERM` might be sufficient now.\r\n\r\nWondering if something similar is going wonky with locales also.\r\n\r\nHmmm. When I ssh into a nixos system, LANG is set to the remote server default value.\r\n\r\nBut when I ssh into a osx system, LANG is not set. If I then set LANG, the problem seems to disappear. How very odd.\r\n\r\nAnd it this case, my LANG setting should be valid I think with just the plan osx system. `en_AU.UTF-8`.",
