    "updated_at": "2024-07-22T10:35:53Z",
    "body": "Proposal: I think the problem is unrelated to starship, so we should switch to another place.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nMy case: setting `LC_CTYPE=C.UTF-8` somewhere also make zsh handle multibyte characters correctly. Either add `export LC_CTYPE=C.UFT-8` in my (remote machine's) `.zshrc`, or use `LC_CTYPE=C.UFT-8 ssh ..`. Only `C.UTF-8` works, other `*.UTF-8` does not (at least I did not find a valid one). Very weird.",
    "author_association": "NONE",
